  "prompt": "How do I apply for improvement in the 12th CBSE exam?",
  "response": "To apply for improvement in the 12th CBSE board exam, follow these steps:\n\n1. Check Eligibility\n- You must have appeared for the CBSE 12th board exam in the previous year\n- You are allowed to improve marks in a maximum of 5 subjects\n\n2. Obtain Improvement Form\n- Visit the official CBSE website (cbse.gov.in)\n- Download the improvement exam application form\n- Alternatively, collect the form from your school\n\n3. Fill the Application Form\n- Complete all required details accurately\n- Attach necessary documents\n- Select the subjects you want to improve\n\n4. Documentation\n- Recent passport-size photograph\n- Copy of previous year's mark sheet\n- School leaving certificate\n- Identity proof\n\n5. Fee Payment\n- Pay the prescribed improvement exam fee\n- Fee can usually be paid online or through challan\n- Fees vary for different subjects\n\n6. Submit Application\n- Submit the completed form to your school or CBSE regional office\n- Ensure timely submission before the specified deadline\n\n7. Important Considerations\n- Only your new/improved marks will be considered\n- You can appear for improvement in theory and practical exams\n\nNote: Always check the latest guidelines and deadlines on the official CBSE website.",
